  "text": "In a study of Wyness et al. [CITATION_1] a different model of handheld digital refractometers was challenged, reporting 4 decimals rather than 3. Wildlife endocrinologists should be encouraged to consider purchasing a similar model with the fourth decimal allowing a higher measurement accuracy, as well as, a multi-scale model in case application in other wildlife or domestic species will also be explored.",
